President Biden has declared a major disaster for the Hoopa Valley Tribe due to severe winter storms and mudslides that occurred from February 14 to March 5, 2023. Federal aid will be provided to supplement the Tribe's efforts in the affected areas. The Hoopa Valley Tribe and certain private nonprofit organizations can receive federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Funding is also available for hazard mitigation measures. Benigno Bern Ruiz of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional assistance may be designated once assessments are completed. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.